How Homer might have handled the passage may perhaps be inferred from B 23-33 = 60-70. There is not a case in Quintus where a command is given to a messenger as such in oratio recta and delivered in oratio recta. What might be regarded as instances of approximation to this are the commands which occur in the speeohes of Odysseus in XII, 25-45, and of the shade of Achilles in XIV, 185-222. The command in the former is not definitely directed, though later fiilfilled by Sinon.
